commit.message:
gui: added the "Split A/V videos" check button.

It toggles the "split_videos" option (renamed from "dash_support"), which will include or exclude streams that have audio and video in separate URLs.

When disabled, videos will load much faster. However, the highest resolution of non-split videos is 720p.

cli: renamed the `--dash!` option to `--split-videos!`, to better reflect the meaning.

Also renamed the config-option `dash_support` to `split_videos`.

commit.message:
- Added the `subscription_videos_per_channel` config-option.

It specifies the number of video results to fetch from each channel when displaying local subscription videos.

Valid values are between 1 and 50. Previously, the default value was 10. Now, the default value is 20.

When a channel publishes more than this many new videos (since last check), only the most N recent ones are fetched.
